<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-03-23T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-03-23T11:00:00-05:00" n="12" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d12">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.7412A/4: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Bulgaria</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-03-23T11:00:00-05:00">March 23, 1928—11
                                a.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>4. This is for your information. Yesterday the Department informed the
                            Bulgarian Minister that it is ready to conclude an arbitration treaty
                            with Bulgaria, identical in effect with the treaty with France, signed
                            February 6, 1928;<note n="2" xml:id="d12fn2"><ref target="frus1928v02#pg_816"><hi rend="italic">ibid.</hi>, 1928,
                                    vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, p. 816</ref>.</note> also a
                            conciliation treaty based on the Bryan treaty with Great Britain, signed
                            September 15, 1914.<note n="3" xml:id="d12fn3"><ref target="frus1914#pg_304"><hi rend="italic">ibid.</hi>, 1914, p.
                                    304</ref>.</note> In about ten days’ time the proposed texts
                            will be furnished the Bulgarian Minister.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>